Initial Scene / Model Setup

Current scene setup:
- Imported submarine model into Unity water scene
- Selected one submarine root object as the physics body
- Added Rigidbody to the submarine root
- Turned off Use Gravity for early testing
(because gravity was active, but buoyancy had not been implemented yet To debug thrust behavior first, gravity was ignored temporarily)
- Created a Thrusters parent object
- Created 8 empty child objects to mark the thruster locations
- Rotated the empties to match the physical thruster placement as closely as possible

Useful Rigid body setup during debugging:
- Use Gravity = Off
- Mass = around 100 during tests
- Linear Damping = increased to reduce drifting
- Angular Damping = increased to reduce flipping / over-rotation
- Interpolate = Interpolate
- Collision Detection = Continuous

